<br>
Memory - DDR goes in in pairs or requires one of those dummy thingies.  If not the system won't boot.<br>
<br>
HD - If she is going to move big data fast like downloading/uploading pics and MP3's then you might wanna think RAID, else one drive will perform better.  RAID = longer seek times.  Be weary of IBM Deskstars, they tend to fail.<br>
<br>
CDRW - Oi! the name is on the tip of my tougue...umm umm been out for a while...err... TDK? Teac?<br>
<br>
What about a NIC and USB 2.0?  You are choking this thorobred to be with a 56K connection.<br>
<br>
Cooling - there is a PCI card cum exhaust fan that I'd recomend that you put right next to the vid card.  It pulls air across the GPU and then out of your box.  It will occupy a PCI slot but seems to work well.  Pretty sure the case already has two or three fans in it. <br>
<br>
