as for hard drives, I personaly have always belived that 2 smaller hard drive will do you better.  2 hard drives gives you the ability to have one drive for basic programs, that will not reall get fragmented, and one for user files (MP3's, game demo's and the like) that will eventualy get fragmented to hell and run like a dog. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uumbrae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Umbrae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.newcreations.net/3d/cubebullet/bulletb_ss1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/18/01 5:25:22 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usaffyredarklove.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saffyre Darklove</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#E9D756>(12/19/01 6:11:08 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.the-nextlevel.com/staff/bahn.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Making a new computer...help please:)</span><hr size=1> Definetly ditch Creative Platinum sound card and go Audigy Platinum!, don't think many people can hear the difference but it's a better card and I believe you got a firewire port on it also.<br>
